name: BLUCHER WITH GUM SOLE
description: Quoddy footwear is hand made in Maine with a history of craftsmanship that dates back to 1909 when founder Harry Smith Shorey began making hand sewn moccasins inspired by Native American craft. By the mid 1950's Quoddy had become synonymous with the quality and beauty of Maine hand sewn footwear. This limited edition capsule collection is a new Incu collaboration with Quoddy and offers a twist on the classic Quoddy aesthetic designed specifically with the Incu customer and Australian market in mind. This Quoddy suede moccasin has a round toe, three lacquared eyelets, rawhide lace, leather lined, gum sole, contrast heel panel                                               Colour: Burgundy/Forest Green
